actions damnable

780
01:19:43,843 --> 01:19:46,713
and deserving of the fate
you brought upon them.

781
01:19:46,747 --> 01:19:48,816
Then you'll be leaving?

782
01:19:48,848 --> 01:19:51,252
Can't do that.

783
01:19:51,284 --> 01:19:55,155
No one hires a gunman
who runs from trouble.

784
01:19:55,189 --> 01:19:59,093
You don't have to run, Dave.
You can walk.

785
01:20:01,227 --> 01:20:05,100
The terms of my employment
would not allow me to do that.

786
01:20:26,253 --> 01:20:30,258
This here LeMat's mighty heavy.
Puts me at a disadvantage.

787
01:20:31,257 --> 01:20:33,226
What would you suggest?

788
01:20:33,260 --> 01:20:36,564
Would you be kind enough
to let me go back inside

789
01:20:36,596 --> 01:20:38,665
and retrieve myself a Colt?

790
01:20:50,744 --> 01:20:53,181
Thank you.

791
01:22:28,641 --> 01:22:31,578
My friend,
you are no longer employed.

792
01:22:42,021 --> 01:22:44,891
It would appear you are correct.

793
01:22:54,534 --> 01:22:57,437
It's been a pleasure
knowing you, Dave.

794
01:23:34,007 --> 01:23:36,444
I'm all right, Pa.

795
01:23:36,744 --> 01:23:40,714
It's not gonna take long for word to
get out on what happened here today.

796
01:23:40,748 --> 01:23:43,571
Men from far and wide
are gonna come looking

797
01:23:43,572 --> 01:23:45,453
for me to make a
name for themselves.

798
01:23:45,485 --> 01:23:48,988
Don't go away. I can't
finish the field on my own.

799
01:23:49,021 --> 01:23:51,958
The field's finished, Pa.
I seeded it.

800
01:23:51,992 --> 01:23:54,829
It'll take care of itself.

801
01:23:54,861 --> 01:23:57,131
I gotta go.

802
01:23:57,163 --> 01:23:59,999
You're not going for
another 10 years, are you?

803
01:24:00,033 --> 01:24:02,770
No, I promise.

804
01:24:02,802 --> 01:24:04,905
See you soon, Pa.

805
01:24:25,859 --> 01:24:28,495
<i>Little is known
of him after that.</i>

806
01:24:28,529 --> 01:24:30,765
<i>Some say he drifted down
to Coffeeville</i>

807
01:24:30,797 --> 01:24:34,001
<i>where he was involved
in another altercation</i>

808
01:24:34,034 --> 01:24:36,437
<i>a few years later.</i>

809
01:24:36,470 --> 01:24:39,740
<i>But those accusations
were never proven.</i>

810
01:24:39,772 --> 01:24:42,743
<i>The common view was
he moved westward</i>

811
01:24:42,775 --> 01:24:44,744
<i>under a different name,</i>

812
01:24:44,778 --> 01:24:48,716
<i>where he lived a life
of quiet isolation.</i>

813
01:24:52,785 --> 01:24:55,756
<i>What is known is that
when Mary Alice died</i>

814
01:24:55,788 --> 01:24:59,659
<i>a few years later, he did not
attend her funeral.</i>

815
01:24:59,693 --> 01:25:03,530
<i>However, many say
the following day,</i>

816
01:25:03,564 --> 01:25:08,535
<i>a faded red ribbon was found
attached to her headstone.</i>

817
01:25:16,642 --> 01:25:19,180
<i>Others in Fowler recounted
stories of seeing him</i>

818
01:25:19,212 --> 01:25:23,650
<i>throughout the years
up until his father's death,</i>

819
01:25:23,684 --> 01:25:27,555
<i>at which time
he came no more.</i>


 

 

 
     
  

  
     

 
										
